27/04/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic said Monday (26 April) he expects the presidential election to be held in December or early January 2005.
He also called for the adoption of a new election law by then to ensure transparency in campaign financing.
Mesic estimated that expenses would total about 527,000 euros and said he has the backing of the Croatian People's Party, but has not approached any other parties for support.
(HINA, Croatian Radio - 26/04/04)
